theorem P3_closed_iff_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 A ↔ IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    -- Since `A` is closed, its closure is itself.
    have h_closure : closure (A : Set X) = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
    -- `P3` provides `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`, hence `A ⊆ interior A`.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
      have : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hP3
      simpa [h_closure] using this
    -- Together with the general inclusion `interior A ⊆ A`, we get equality.
    have h_eq : (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) :=
      Set.Subset.antisymm h_subset interior_subset
    -- An equality with an open set yields that `A` is open.
    simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior
  · intro hA_open
    exact Topology.P3_of_isOpen (A := A) hA_open

theorem P1_interior_closure_iff_P3_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ↔
      Topology.P3 (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
  have h₁ := P1_interior_closure_iff_P2_interior_closure (A := A)
  have h₂ := P3_interior_closure_iff_P2_interior_closure (A := A)
  simpa using h₁.trans h₂.symm
